---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Nokturna', item: new URL('/nokturna', SITE.url).href },
  ],
};
---
<Base
  title="Nokturna Card Game in Moonlight Peaks — How to Play, Cards & Tips | Moonlit Almanac"
  description="A guide to Nokturna, the in-game card game in Moonlight Peaks: how it works, where to collect cards, how to play residents, and winning strategies — updated at launch."
  path="/nokturna"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Nokturna' }]}
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Cards</p>
      <h1>Nokturna — the <em>Moonlight Peaks</em> card game</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Nokturna is the town's favorite card game: collect cards and challenge residents to a match.
        This entry will hold the full card list, deck tips, and a how-to-win guide. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>What we know</h2>
      <p>
        From the official store details, Nokturna is a collectible card minigame woven into daily
        life — you gather cards and play against the townsfolk of Moonlight Peaks. Card-game side
        modes like this tend to become a favorite long-term activity, with their own unlocks and
        opponents to beat.
      </p>

      <h2>Coming at launch ({GAME.releaseLabel})</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Full card list</strong> — every card, its stats, and how to obtain it.</li>
        <li><strong>How to play</strong> — the rules, turn structure, and win conditions, step by step.</li>
        <li><strong>Best decks</strong> — starter-friendly builds and answers to tough opponents.</li>
        <li><strong>Opponent guide</strong> — which residents play Nokturna and what they reward.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Placeholder entry, intentionally. The card data only exists once the full game ships on
        {GAME.releaseLabel}; we'll populate this within hours of launch. This is the page most likely
        to own its niche — almost nobody documents in-game card games early.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
